Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.25,0:00:32.21,Signs,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1528,188)\blur0.25\fs33\fnGeorgia\fsp3.0\c&HF8CC9E&\t(2529,5824,\c&HFAFBFA&)\pos(326,245)}Beyond Journey's End
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.97,0:01:33.97,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}29 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin the Bier region, located on the Northern Plateau
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.04,0:01:43.11,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I guess there are cities \Non the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.11,0:01:45.01,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There are a lot of bars here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.45,0:01:49.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This area's the only grain-producing \Nregion on the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.93,0:01:52.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's always had plenty of breweries.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.92,0:01:54.67,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.67,0:01:56.80,Default,CUSTOMER A,0000,0000,0000,,I was talking to Old Man Fass.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.10,0:01:59.60,Default,CUSTOMER A,0000,0000,0000,,He said he's almost found Boshaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.06,0:02:01.42,Default,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.42,0:02:04.38,DefaultTop,CUSTOMER B,0000,0000,0000,,He's been talking about that \Nsince my grandpa was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.26,0:02:04.76,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What's Boshaft?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.76,0:02:07.23,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard about it from Mr. Heiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.46,0:02:11.87,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, most of the continent was \Nruled by a single great empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.87,0:02:15.53,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,It was an exquisite liquor \Noffered to the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.53,0:02:16.74,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.05,0:02:20.63,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,He would lament about how, because of \NMs. Frieren, he never got to drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.70,0:02:25.63,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,There was a reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.24,0:02:33.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to stay here for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.70,0:02:34.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Once we're finished shopping—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.86,0:02:35.64,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.36,0:02:38.75,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It's you, Frieren!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.98,0:02:44.08,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't seen you in a century.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.08,0:02:46.53,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's been eighty years, Fass.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.53,0:02:50.23,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,You're a stickler for details now? \NHow unlike you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.20,0:02:54.27,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Your roster's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:57.62,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,That young guy who liked \Nto drink isn't with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.92,0:02:59.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Heiter's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.29,0:03:01.86,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He went peacefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.16,0:03:07.33,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I was too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.98,0:03:13.73,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I've located Boshaft, \Nthe Emperor's Spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:15.28,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Will you help me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.28,0:03:17.73,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,You can use magic, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.43,0:03:21.84,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What does magic have to do with Boshaft?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.36,0:03:24.03,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me, and you'll see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.56,0:03:33.07,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It's in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.07,0:03:36.18,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Is this... a mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.18,0:03:38.93,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I dug it all by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.71,0:03:45.31,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Most people think all dwarves are miners,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:48.33,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,but I grew up in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:50.28,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I had to study mining from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.08,0:03:55.34,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I did it for that legendary liquor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.32,0:03:58.83,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.83,0:04:01.72,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fass. No one loves liquor as much as him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.22,0:04:06.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He's spent over two hundred years \Nlooking for Boshaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.77,0:04:10.09,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He asked us for help \Nthe last time we met,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.47,0:04:15.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but we had a Demon King to defeat \Nat the time, so we said no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.35,0:04:18.36,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,But Boshaft!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.69,0:04:18.36,FlashbackTop,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Let go!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.85,0:04:24.95,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Pulling Heiter away was no mean feat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:29.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you digging a mine \Nto find liquor?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.23,0:04:36.38,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,According to legend, there's Boshaft \Nstored in the ruins underground here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.05,0:04:41.38,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,And two hundred years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.38,0:04:46.14,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,when I found this stone monument, \NI knew it was true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.83,0:04:48.76,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,This is ancient elvish.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:53.58,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,The inscription proclaims that Boshaft is \Nthe greatest liquor to have ever existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:56.27,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,"Milliarde."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.44,0:04:59.99,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps that's who wrote \Nthis inscription.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.55,0:05:06.48,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,You're well-educated if you can \Nread ancient elvish at your age.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.25,0:05:10.99,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren drilled it into me \Nwhen I was young.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.50,0:05:15.13,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Most grimoires are written \Nin ancient elvish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.13,0:05:17.38,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to learn to read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.34,0:05:24.41,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,So it was Milliarde.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.76,0:05:31.26,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since discovering this inscription, \NI've dedicated my life to finding Boshaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.64,0:05:35.26,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,And now, it's almost within my grasp.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.84,0:05:37.71,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You found the ruins?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.16,0:05:41.62,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,The ruins themselves, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.33,0:05:47.14,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,But as you can see, the doors to \Nthis stone chamber won't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.14,0:05:51.28,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,A powerful barrier was erected \Nto preserve the liquor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.59,0:05:54.85,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to break it, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.26,0:05:59.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.58,0:06:01.89,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.89,0:06:04.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It'll take time to remove.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.75,0:06:06.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Those kids wouldn't be happy about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.93,0:06:09.25,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make it worth your while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:10.79,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,With a grimoire?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:14.18,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Money! I'll pay you twenty \NReich gold coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.65,0:06:18.48,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even worth considering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.02,0:06:20.69,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Frieren!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.97,0:06:24.20,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It's my dream to drink Boshaft!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.20,0:06:26.70,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I've been searching for \Nover two hundred years!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.50,0:06:30.70,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.36,0:06:37.70,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, perhaps we could help him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:40.84,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I feel sorry for Old Man Fass.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.13,0:06:43.43,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about? \NYou're giving me the creeps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.43,0:06:45.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, you'd be opposed \Nto this sort of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:49.34,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, he's offering twenty gold \Ncoins. We can use that on our journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.34,0:06:50.31,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's a ton of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.31,0:06:52.73,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We won't have to worry about \Nliving expenses for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.73,0:06:54.22,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.22,0:06:57.97,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But the barrier will take \Nthree months to remove.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.97,0:06:59.31,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,That's hardly any time at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.31,0:07:00.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.65,0:07:03.23,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:06.35,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't come crying to me later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.65,0:07:27.17,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the final stages \Nof removing the barrier.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.62,0:07:30.13,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We should be able to finish tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.15,0:07:35.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,You don't look very pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:42.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess not.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.46,0:07:46.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Boshaft doesn't taste good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.02,0:07:50.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not worth devoting your life to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.06,0:07:52.04,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But the inscription said...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.95,0:07:59.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Some elves pass the time \Nin ways you wouldn't believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.82,0:08:17.85,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Milliarde, you never do anything. \NYou just gaze off into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:24.50,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,Many of our fellow elves spend their \Nlong lives searching for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.50,0:08:26.06,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think that is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.50,0:08:27.58,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.34,0:08:30.85,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,So that they don't end up like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.32,0:08:36.64,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, could you imagine the thing \Nyou spent your life searching for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.64,0:08:40.33,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,turning out to be worthless garbage?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.82,0:08:43.83,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.20,0:08:48.09,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,My distant past.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.91,0:08:55.09,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,This liquor really is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.61,0:08:57.32,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Boshaft.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.32,0:09:01.09,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the awful, cheap liquor \Nthey served at the coronation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.80,0:09:07.11,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,Before coming to this village, \NI carved an inscription to pass the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.52,0:09:11.26,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,It says, "Boshaft is the greatest \Nliquor to have ever existed."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.16,0:09:14.23,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What was the point of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.97,0:09:18.17,Flashback,MILLIARDE,0000,0000,0000,,There was no point at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.71,0:09:24.35,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It's finally time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.29,0:09:47.49,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It's well-preserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.49,0:09:51.49,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought I'd get to taste this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.72,0:09:55.14,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Let's toast. Drink with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.77,0:10:07.20,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.02,0:10:16.00,FlashbackItalics,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren, why did you decline \Nto search for Boshaft?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.59,0:10:21.02,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Heiter, you like liquor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:22.51,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:24.94,Flashback,HIMMEL,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to this corrupt priest.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:28.78,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do if the liquor \Nyou spent your life searching for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.78,0:10:31.24,Flashback,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,turned out to be unbelievably terrible?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.87,0:10:37.43,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.91,0:10:39.36,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'd laugh it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.74,0:10:44.23,Flashback,HEITER,0000,0000,0000,,It tastes bad, right? Then it's \Nbest enjoyed with friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.87,0:10:50.72,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It's so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.83,0:10:54.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.71,0:10:57.75,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the worst-tasting drink \NI've ever had.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.66,0:11:04.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you just watching? Try it, Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.08,0:11:07.19,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What? No way. It's terrible, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.19,0:11:08.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.72,0:11:14.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,It's freaking gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.86,0:11:20.50,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Why is it so gross?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.20,0:11:23.15,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,It really is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.15,0:11:24.14,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.28,0:11:28.20,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,There's plenty to go around!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.20,0:11:30.86,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make the whole city suffer with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.63,0:11:35.87,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.87,0:11:41.26,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,My search ended in disappointment, \Nbut I've never had such a fun night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.52,0:11:44.63,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad you guys were here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.21,0:11:50.56,Default,FASS,0000,0000,0000,,Liquor's meant to be \Nenjoyed with good times.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.02,0:12:06.03,Signs_EpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\c&HFAFFF7&\pos(344,269.5)}Episode 33: Logistics in the Northern Plateau
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.03,0:12:10.03,Signs_WText,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur0.2\pos(588.5,16)}30 years after the death of Himmel the Hero,\Nin Norm Company territory, located on the Northern Plateau
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.72,0:12:15.67,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your share of bread, Mr. Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.97,0:12:23.04,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that? \NThis bread just went "clunk."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.62,0:12:26.05,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a sound food should make.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.31,0:12:30.28,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We've been eating rock-hard \Nbread this whole week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:32.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Don't complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.37,0:12:38.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The Northern Plateau is barren outside \Nof the grain-producing Bier region,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.20,0:12:42.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and goods aren't even circulating now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.67,0:12:46.06,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be eating mostly this while \Nwe camp, at the very least.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.12,0:12:48.62,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.62,0:12:53.52,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,If we walk another half day, \Nwe should be able to get a decent meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.21,0:13:09.64,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,That's an impressive fortress city.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.23,0:13:12.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the Norm Company's estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.54,0:13:14.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That structure in the center \Nis their headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.84,0:13:20.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They deal in various goods, \Nprimarily wheat from the Bier region.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.75,0:13:23.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They're an armed trading company \Nwith the logistics network
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.58,0:13:28.76,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,and military force to supply the villages \Ndotted across the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:31.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Not even the state can touch them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.69,0:13:36.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,For all intents and purposes, they rule \Nhumanity on the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.08,0:13:40.32,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,But Ms. Frieren, you said earlier \Nthat goods aren't circulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.87,0:13:42.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,That's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.95,0:13:46.80,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the specific cause, \Nbut things change over time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.41,0:13:51.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe the Norm Company \Nisn't as strong as it once was.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.94,0:13:57.69,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But it's likely that they still have a lot\Nof influence on the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.69,0:14:00.40,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We should avoid making waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.09,0:14:10.09,Default,RECEPTIONIST,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.81,0:14:13.33,Default,RECEPTIONIST,0000,0000,0000,,So you're Ms. Fern, a first-class mage.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.94,0:14:15.59,Default,RECEPTIONIST,0000,0000,0000,,You may pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.82,0:14:19.13,Default,RECEPTIONIST,0000,0000,0000,,That person...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.86,0:14:30.49,Default,RECEPTIONIST,0000,0000,0000,,One moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.24,0:14:33.92,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.10,0:14:42.56,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,I am Norm, the company president.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.00,0:14:46.17,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, mage of the party of heroes,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.17,0:14:51.63,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,you will be paying off the debt \Nyou've owed for eighty years in full.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:55.95,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Frieren, you've been carrying debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.27,0:14:57.47,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.47,0:14:58.70,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.70,0:15:01.96,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But I was told I could \Npay it back anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.17,0:15:04.78,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what the documents say.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.46,0:15:07.76,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Verbal agreements are no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.76,0:15:14.00,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,It seems my predecessor's predecessor \Nwas lax in that area, but I am not.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.16,0:15:22.30,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Three Strahl gold, twenty Reich gold, \Nand various silvers and coppers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.15,0:15:25.72,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,You're as wealthy as a minor noble.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.72,0:15:26.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.56,0:15:32.32,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Your grandfather did us a favor, \Nso you can keep the change.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.54,0:15:35.32,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.10,0:15:39.13,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't nearly enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.01,0:15:44.94,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I have to work in the mines \Nfor three hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.94,0:15:48.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,My journey ends here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.55,0:15:53.84,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Ms. Frieren?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.84,0:15:56.59,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you dressed like that? \NWhere's your bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.03,0:16:00.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They took everything as collateral.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.55,0:16:20.23,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Bye, Fern and Stark.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.49,0:16:21.74,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.61,0:16:25.75,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.99,0:16:28.68,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.67,0:16:32.71,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is buy back Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.71,0:16:34.86,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,She's not a thing, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.38,0:16:39.38,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, there's nothing \Nyou can do about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.67,0:16:40.84,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.89,0:16:46.37,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,According to the documents,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.37,0:16:48.89,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,she owes over five hundred Strahl \Ngold coins including interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.89,0:16:51.26,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Even when converted to Reich gold coins,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.26,0:16:54.40,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,the most trusted currency on the Northern \NPlateau, she owes over three hundred.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.40,0:16:57.90,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can procure such a sum?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.61,0:17:00.42,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,No, that would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.42,0:17:02.37,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, what are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.05,0:17:05.80,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,We can't wait three hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.61,0:17:14.91,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really like mines.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.91,0:17:17.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,They're hot and dusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.38,0:17:31.40,Default,MINER,0000,0000,0000,,The president told us \Nabout you, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.29,0:17:34.39,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.77,0:17:36.73,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we get started, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.39,0:18:30.28,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We'll go straight through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.03,0:18:32.66,Default,MINER,0000,0000,0000,,You're certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.21,0:18:35.54,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.35,0:18:40.73,Default,MINER,0000,0000,0000,,All right, boys! Start digging!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.73,0:18:41.94,Default,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.39,0:18:58.56,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,The Norm Company president \Nof two generations ago
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.92,0:19:02.58,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,started out as a backwater noble \Ncast out to the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.20,0:19:09.77,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,He was a great man who invested in this \Nbarren land and built a logistics network,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.77,0:19:13.38,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,bringing stability to people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.90,0:19:19.34,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,At the time, nobody expected \Nmuch from our party of heroes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.34,0:19:22.60,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,but he provided us with funds \Nwith no repayment deadline.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.35,0:19:30.08,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought I'd be treated \Nlike this by his grandson.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:37.19,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,But there must be a reason you came \Nall the way to this mine, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.45,0:19:42.26,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Logistics in the Northern Plateau \Nare in a terrible state, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.69,0:19:44.07,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.07,0:19:48.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Even my companions complained that \Nthey'd never eaten such hard bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.57,0:19:51.95,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they hadn't. \NI'm not fond of it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.97,0:19:55.70,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Since conditions have worsened here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.29,0:20:01.96,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,we've lost a third of our armed \Ncaravans and army fighting demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.36,0:20:07.97,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Our logistics network is in ruins, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.66,0:20:12.80,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,If the Norm Company were a nation, \Nwe'd have fallen already.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.36,0:20:20.59,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,However, we are a trading company.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.54,0:20:26.18,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we have the funds, \Nwe can always rebuild.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.54,0:20:32.74,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,When you arrived in this region, I felt \Nthe Goddess must've brought you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.49,0:20:39.32,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,That scrap of paper representing your \Nparty's debt gained tremendous value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.39,0:20:43.57,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,This mine is still under development.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.57,0:20:46.62,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,If we strike silver ore, \Nwe'll turn a huge profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.62,0:20:50.74,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Enough to forgive the party \Nof heroes' debt and more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.18,0:20:55.76,Default,NROM,0000,0000,0000,,It should be easy for you \Nto find, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.32,0:21:01.93,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you're using that \Nscrap of paper to coerce me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.96,0:21:07.81,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,If our logistics network falls apart \Nentirely, many people will starve and die.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.26,0:21:13.13,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Please save the people of the \NNorthern Plateau, Ms. Frieren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.88,0:21:18.94,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,Also, if you help us, you'll \Nhave soft bread to eat
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.94,0:21:22.96,Default,NORM,0000,0000,0000,,even in the farthest reaches \Nof the Northern Plateau.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.81,0:21:27.10,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,You're as shrewd as your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.50,0:21:30.18,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,This is why I can't stand merchants.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.77,0:21:33.57,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. You have a deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.16,0:21:38.26,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, I intended to repay \Nthe debt I owed your grandfather.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:47.62,Default,MINER,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe we \Nactually struck silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.62,0:21:58.20,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back. Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.99,0:22:03.66,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, good. We were discussing \Nhow to save you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.66,0:22:06.60,Default,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning to raid the mine tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.12,0:22:10.15,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh. You're so hot-headed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.82,0:22:15.59,Default,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, from now on, \Nwe'll get to eat soft bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.38,0:22:19.21,Default,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.98,0:22:25.11,Credits,CREDITS,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(526,517)\fs10\pos(525,120)}Translation\N{\fs12}Sho Stifler\N\N{\fs10}Editing & Typesetting\N{\fs12}Geoff Mazzolini\N\N{\fs10}Subtitle Timing\N{\fs12}Edgar Cruz\N\N{\fs10}Quality Check\N{\fs12}Alicia Ashby\N\N{\fs10}Translation Check\N{\fs12}Elizabeth Ellis
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.07,0:23:52.53,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.62,0:23:52.52,DefaultOverlap,STARK,0000,0000,0000,,I'll help you bury them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.68,0:23:53.31,DefaultTop,CAPTAIN,0000,0000,0000,,Protect the villagers!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.55,0:23:54.81,Default,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Someone like that can't be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.09,0:23:55.41,DefaultOverlap,FRIEREN,0000,0000,0000,,We were a bit too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.50,0:23:55.51,DefaultTop,CHILDHOOD FRIEND,0000,0000,0000,,Demons destroyed the village...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.97,0:23:57.23,DefaultOverlapTop,FERN,0000,0000,0000,,There are so few of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.80,0:23:57.12,DefaultTop,GENAU,0000,0000,0000,,Are you praying?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.40,0:24:00.11,Default,METHODE,0000,0000,0000,,So Ms. Fern also received \Na demon-slaying request.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.66,0:24:00.07,Signs_NextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(229,1)\blur3\t(20,312,\blur0.2)\pos(320,113.5)\c&H000000&\t(312,646,\c&HF6F6F6&)\fsp1.6\t(\fsp1)}Episode 34\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\NA Demon-Slaying Request